I was concerned that the DB filtering would be broken now that vm_state can be a list of values for the API but it looks like the DB code checks the filter value to see if it's a list and if so, it queries with IN(x,y,z) so that should be OK:

That happens down here:

https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/db/sqlalchemy/api.py#L279

and the list of legal keys is here:

https://github.com/openstack/nova/blob/master/nova/db/sqlalchemy/api.py#L1914

So if you do a nova list and filter on status 'resize' and there are instances in state 'active' or 'stopped' you should get those back with this change.

I'm -1 for the hacking nit (need to continue lines by wrapping in parenthesis rather than using \) but after that is fixed I think I'm +1."}, {'account_id': 8651, 'date': '2013-11-10 03:04:41.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 8.'}, {'account_id': 8651, 'date': '2013-11-10 03:08:54.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 7: (1 inline comment)

commit_message:
Add status mapping for shutoff instance when resize

Current code always map instance's status into Shutoff when
getting status of resizing instance with power_state shutoff.
This isn't consistent with active instance, we should add
status mapping for power-off resizing instance.

Closes-Bug: #1247106
Co-Authored-By: chenxiao <chenxiao@cn.ibm.com>
Change-Id: Id4bff71b2c46ec9dccea6d8ac36eba273e48ea5d

revisions:
[{'created': '2013-11-16 11:00:50.000000000', 'message': 'libvirt: host update disable/enable report HTTP 400

When disable/enable host with host-update command, end user will
get HTTP 400 error even if the host was updated(disabled/enabled)
successfully.

The root cause is that after the host was disabled/enabled, nova
api need depend on host status result to check if the host was
disabled or enabled, but libvirt driver did not return host status
to nova api.

Change-Id: I0688134eecb0628b680c8ed01741f00f80eec53f
Closes-Bug: # 1251589

commit_message:
libvirt: host update disable/enable report HTTP 400

When disable/enable host with host-update command, end user will
get HTTP 400 error even if the host was updated(disabled/enabled)
successfully.

The root cause is that after the host was disabled/enabled, nova
api need depend on host status result to check if the host was
disabled or enabled, but libvirt driver did not return host status
to nova api.

Change-Id: I0688134eecb0628b680c8ed01741f00f80eec53f
Closes-Bug: #1251589

[{'created': '2013-11-13 14:43:17.000000000', 'message': "Recover from IMAGE-* state on compute manager start-up

If a compute manager is stopped / fails during certain IMAGE-*
operations then the instance will be left stuck in a transitional
task_state

This change handles three possible task states IMAGE_PENDING_UPLOAD,
IMAGE_UPLOADING, and IMAGE_SNAPSHOT.

Both IMAGE_PENDING_UPLOAD and IMAGE_UPLOADING are task states set
after the request has gotten to the compute manager and so we can
clear these safely knwing the operation has ended/failed with the
restart of the compute manager.

With IMAGE-SNAPSHOT it's possible this state was set in the API so
we revert the instance to a task_state of None but the change also
makes provision to set the task_state to IMAGE-SNAPSHOT once the
request comes thrpough to the compute manager so the current
operation is clear once it begins again after the compute manager is
back up and running.

Partial-Bug: #1250869
Change-Id: I665c0ec735968aa0d7553dfc0cfb2373f93451f6

commit_message:
Recover from IMAGE-* state on compute manager start-up

If a compute manager is stopped / fails during certain IMAGE-*
operations then the instance will be left stuck in a transitional
task_state

This change handles three possible task states IMAGE_PENDING_UPLOAD,
IMAGE_UPLOADING, and IMAGE_SNAPSHOT.

Both IMAGE_PENDING_UPLOAD and IMAGE_UPLOADING are task states set
after the request has gotten to the compute manager and so we can
clear these safely knowing the operation has ended/failed with the
restart of the compute manager.

With IMAGE-SNAPSHOT it's possible this state was set in the API so
we revert the instance to a task_state of None but the change also
makes provision to set the task_state to IMAGE-SNAPSHOT once the
request comes through to the compute manager so the current
operation is clear once it begins again after the compute manager is
back up and running.

Related to blueprint recover-stuck-state

commit_message:
handle migration errors

handle errors:
   MigrationPreCheckError, NoValidHost,
   InvalidSharedStorage and InvalidLocalStorage
in _migrate_live so that the 'reason' is passed up

Closes-Bug: 1250523

Change-Id: I3d7e0626223f2606c5e7205e5022e26585506cfb

If you added one, I'd definitely be +1 again."}, {'account_id': 1779, 'date': '2013-11-25 10:16:07.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 5: Looks good to me (core reviewer)

I don't think we should block this fix on a test case for an unrelated codepath. By all means add a test case for this codepath as a separate patch, though in fact I think we should just delete the 'api_thread_pool' config parameter entirely. Nova is unusable in production if you set api_thread_pool=False because libvirt native API calls will block all greenthreads. The config param was only added because the person who wrote the thread pool code was afraid of regressions for existing deployments. We've had this code for enough releases now that we should just make it unconditional, at which point the test case question becomes moot anyway."}, {'account_id': 6969, 'date': '2013-11-25 10:29:24.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 5: (1 inline comment)

commit_message:
Use of logging in native thread causes deadlock connecting to libvirtd

When connecting to libvirtd daemon we were calling the _connect
method in a native thread. The use of logging in this method hit this
bug in eventlet https://bitbucket.org/eventlet/eventlet/issue/137/
causing nova-compute to hang.

Closes-Bug: #1252409

Change-Id: I0d22c3ed1b3288aeb1afae130f11a4f38dc6440a

Okay, I'm concerned that this code appears to have reimplemented the synchronized decorator for some reason.  But that's not relevant to your problem here.

I think the proper fix for this is to wrap the tests using the lockutils main().  That ensures that the locks on the database are global and not specific to one single test (which doesn't help if two tests that use the postgres db are running in parallel).

The docstring for the function should explain how to use it: https://github.com/openstack/oslo-incubator/blob/master/openstack/common/lockutils.py#L284  Just add the wrapper to tox.ini as part of the test command.

Since this reimplemented lock decorator appears to support the *_LOCK_PATH env var that should work.  Let me know if you see any problems with it.  Thanks."}, {'account_id': 6722, 'date': '2013-11-24 08:48:56.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't merge this

commit_message:
Fix LockFailed error when testing pgsql migrations

test_migrations was creating a global lock file for pgsql migrations,
instead of using a per-test temp dir to store the lock files. This was
resulting in errors such as:

http://logs.openstack.org/16/56516/9/check/gate-ironic-python27/4d9b449/console.html

This patch restores the previous behavior of using a fixtures.TempDir()
for each test run.

Change-Id: Iad123fc2f4bb7b99bb8ae046b9e1f0a5eea7ad56

commit_message:
Use six.iteritems for python 3.3 support in apiclient module

In python 3, dict type does not have iteritems method. So use
six.iteritems for compatibility in apiclient module.

Part of blueprint make-python3-compatible

Change-Id: I5dd0ea8f38f775d89be9b5f8743a273bf2a7520f

commit_message:
fix: cache contract for memcached backend

set() should return a boolean. Currently, it always returns None. This
one-line fix resolves this issue.

Change-Id: I9d2827891dc8ee8904f3031ea75e5bef0ce30488

commit_message:
Fix downgrade in migration

Fixes a downgrade bug caused by a portprofile_bindings table
definition mismatch between 2a6d0b51f4bb_cisco_plugin_cleanup
and the initial definition.

Change-Id: I051e5b41a4285b6cf24270ea6229b1bbca42106d
Closes-Bug: #1250454

commit_message:
Add search_opts into the method list() for VolumeTypeManager

Since the method base.ManagerWithFind.findall has been modified by
adding the search_opts for all tenants support, the parameter
search_opts should also be added to all the manager classes, which
can be called whithin this method. volumetypemanager does not have
this parameter for its method list(). Adding search_opts will resolve
this issue.

Closes-Bug: #1252665

Change-Id: I526500625f1b5483cb5d88ea15e6ac8485a66ae3

commit_message:
Refactor new options into a new config file.

From now on all releases configurations will be available, which will make
easier to test more than two versions upgrade (meaning test upgrades like
g->h->i).
Notes:
 * from-folsom files will not be necessary since we don't test
folsom->grizzly.
 * from-havana files will be added in the next patch(with the change-id follow
change-id Iac520a8de4c3b9f14e2289cfb9b6a50c4ab0ce32).

Change-Id: I3312732b8c344ce8844a82282a032e383e07e07c

commit_message:
Add workaround for OSError raised by Popen.communicate()

Python 2.6 can raise OSError when too much data is
written to STDIN and the process died prematurely.

In the case of keystoneclient this happens during
the first cms_verify() call of a process. The calling
logic expects a useful error message in order to
refetch the CA or singing CERT, which is missing in the
case of an OSError. So just fake it instead.

Add basic unit tests to cover all of the public methods from
keystone.common.cms, raising test coverage to 77%. Add
unit test for this specific bug (test_cms_verify_token_no_oserror).

Closes-Bug: LP Bug#1235252

Change-Id: I6e650ab9494c605b4e41c78c87a9505e09d5fc29

commit_message:
Fixes wrong hrefs when getting set of messages

Based on current implement, an additional path /messages will be
added, see http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack/marconi/queues
/transport/wsgi/messages.py#L208
However, the /messages path has been already included in the URL.
So this fix just remove it and use req.path directly.

Fixes bug 1240897

Change-Id: Ie4bf6d3df62a5b861a8fe8c6392eb8bd6bf57c2c

[{'created': '2013-11-22 15:43:24.000000000', 'message': 'Python 3.x incompatible use of print operator

The print method should be used with parenthesis in order to keep Python 3.x compatibility.
The file verify_tempest_config.py has 3 print methods breaking this compatibility.

Closes-Bug: #1253718

Change-Id: Ib65f70a9d42d2611c51203e80dc59480775d8adb
'}, {'created': '2013-11-28 12:27:44.000000000', 'message': 'Python 3.x incompatible use of print operator

Fixes for comments done in the code review

Closes-Bug: #1253718

Change-Id: Ib65f70a9d42d2611c51203e80dc59480775d8adb
'}]

Python 3.x incompatible use of print operator

Closes-Bug: #1253718

commit_message:
Add a note about permissions to ceilometer logging directory

In case of swift monitoring swift needs to init logger for ceilometer.
So it needs to have corresponding permissions on log dir.

Change-Id: I67b4b8e438f7d51dba0575ffaacc0d43ef5040da

commit_message:
Adds id in update_floatingip API in PLUMgrid plugin driver

The id parameter is missing in the update_floatingip API, this patch
adds it.

Change-Id: I7407fe34628f8ef03a946a11fea9dad8b0f6c256
Closes-Bug: #1257119
